onour, adore</tr_> him, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:2:719\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.719</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0001.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:897\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.897</biblScope> </bibl>: of things, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τεὸν οἶκον ταῦτα πορσύνοντ᾽</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg002.perseus-grc1:4:151\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ P.\">P.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.151</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τῶν δ᾽ Ὁμήρου καὶ τόδε . . ῥῆμα πόρσυν᾽</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">regard, esteem</tr_> it, ib.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg002.perseus-grc1:278\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">278</biblScope></bibl>.—Both forms are found in Pi.and <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.R.\">A.R.</a></author></bibl>, only <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">πορσύνω</foreign> in Prose and prob. always to be read in Trag. (never found in Com.): <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">πορσανέουσα</foreign> was read by <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Aristarch.</author> </bibl> in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:411\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.411</biblScope></bibl>, but <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">πορσυνέουσα</foreign> most codd., as in Od.ll.cc.: <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">πορσύνων, -ουσα</foreign> are expld. by <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐρεθίζων, -ουσα</foreign> in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl> (leg. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀροθυν-</foreign>).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}